An **SWP for retirement** uses your mutual fund corpus to generate monthly income through systematic withdrawals. Unlike an annuity (which is locked-in for life), SWP keeps your corpus invested and growing, making it a more flexible and tax-efficient source of retirement income. Long-term equity SWP gains are taxed at a lower LTCG rate vs FD interest at slab rate.
